  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Renovation of Handmaids Catholic Clinic and Maternity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will be undertaken by the Sisters of the Congregation of the Handmaids of the Holy Child Jesus (HHCJ) working in Pendembu, Kailahun District. The Sisters run a primary healthcare facility called Handmaids Catholic Clinic and Maternity. They are involved in the following health activities: Out-patient consultations, In-patient treatment, Antenatal care, Postnatal care, Growth monitoring of Under-5&apos;s, Laboratory services, Institutional delivery, Mobile clinics in villages and referral services. 

CAFOD will support the Sisters with renovation of the clinic and purchasing of medical equipment and supplies.</narrative>
  </description>
